<DIV1 TYPE="title page">
<PB REF="003651_0002_10023C4C5012A3A8" MS="y">
<P><HI>The Scripture-Bi&s;hop</HI> VINDICATED</P>
<P>A Defence of the <HI>Dialogue</HI> Between <HI>Praelaticus</HI> and <HI>Eleutherius,</HI> Upon <HI>The</HI> SCRIPTURE-BISHOP, or <HI>The Divine Right of Presbyterian Ordination and Government:</HI> Again&s;t The Exceptions of a Pamphlet, Intitled, <HI>The Scripture-Bi&s;hop</HI> EXAMIN'D</P>
<P>By ELEUTHERIUS, V.D.M.</P>
<P>In a LETTER to a Friend.</P>
<Q><BIBL><HI>I&s;ai. lxvi. 5.</HI></BIBL>
<P>Hear the word of the <HI>LORD,</HI> ye that tremble at his word; Your brethren that hated you, that ca&s;t you out for my name's &s;ake, &s;aid, Let the <HI>LORD</HI> be glorified: but he &s;hall appear to your joy, and they &s;hall be a&s;hamed.</P></Q>
<P>BOSTON, New England: Printed by S. KNEELAND &amp; T. GREEN, for D. HENCHMAN in Cornhill. 1733.</P>
</DIV1>
